{{refimprove|date=June 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Koululainen | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = Elli Mäkilä, since October 2012 | editor_title = | frequency = Monthly | circulation = almost 41200 (2006) | category = Children's magazine | company = | publisher = Otavamedia Oy | firstdate = {{start date and age|1944}} | finaldate = | country = [[Finland]] | based = Helsinki | language = [[Finnish language|Finnish]] | website = http://koululainen.fi/ | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Koululainen''''' ({{lang-fi|Schoolchild}}) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] magazine directed at children and youths.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Peter Hunt|author2=Sheila G. Bannister Ray|title=International Companion Encyclopedia of Children's Literature|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z3ungKFWU4EC&pg=PA441|accessdate=10 February 2015|year=1996|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-08856-5|page=441}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''Koululainen'' was founded in 1944. The magazine is published monthly by Otavamedia Oy and has its headquarters in Helsinki.<ref name="aik">{{cite web|title=Koululainen|url=http://www.aikakauslehdet.fi/ratecards/?vuosi=2015&id=370&lang=eng&type=|work=Aikakauslehdet|accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] of the magazine is ''Elli Mäkilä''. The target audience is children age 7-12 years.<ref name="aik"/> It treats, among other things, schooling, music, books, pets and sport. The magazine is published monthly. In addition to articles, the magazine contains lots of different competitions. A special, thicker, issue called ''Räppäri'', appears in the summer.
