'''Maths Pathway''' is an [[Educational technology|online educational]] [[website]] based in [[Melbourne]], used in Australian [[school]]s to teach [[mathematics]]. It differs from [[traditional mathematics]] teaching, as it is set up in a [[Modularity|modular]] format, with students working on individual pieces of learning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mathspathway.com|title=Home – Maths Pathway|website=www.mathspathway.com|date=2017|language=en|access-date=2017-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://teachforaustralia.org/2016/04/25/impact-case-study-maths-pathway/ |title=Impact Case Study: Maths Pathway |last= |first= |date=25 April 2016 |website=Teach For Australia |publisher= |access-date= 18 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
== History == Maths Pathway was created in 2015 by Richard Wilson and Justin Matthys, both teachers that had experienced their nation's decline in mathematics rankings and were concerned about [[automation]] leading to jobs requiring higher mathematical skill. It started out as a small website headquartered in a shed in Matthys' lawn, but has grown to be featured in over 170+ schools<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/australian-teachers-devise-better-pathway-to-maths-learning/news-story/2096bc39df60bfdf08f3cf4fdc23a231 |title= Australian teachers devise better pathway to maths learning |last=Burrell |first=Andrew |date=10 August 2016 |website=[[The Australian]] |publisher=NewsCorp Australia |access-date=18 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref> and is used by 12,000+ students.<ref name="Pangaea">{{cite web |url=https://www.pangaeaimpact.com/single-post/2016/12/06/Pangaea-Impact-invests-in-Maths-Pathway |title=Pangaea invests in Maths Pathway|last=Bohm |first=Anthony |date=6 December 2016 |website=Pangaea Impact Assessments |publisher= |access-date= 18 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref> Wilson and Matthys hope to have most Australian schools use it eventually.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/nab-meet-the-changemakers/2016/jan/12/new-teaching-model-gets-better-results-from-students |title=New teaching model gets better results from students|last= |first= |date=12 January 2016 |website=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=Guardian News and Media Ltd. |access-date= 18 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
== Features == Math Pathway uses a modular format where students select their work based on what proficiency level they are at, as opposed to every student completing the same tasks. Students are then required to be [[Test (assessment)|tested]] on what they have learned every [[fortnight]]. To use Maths Pathway, schools must pay a fee for each student.<ref name="Pangaea" />
